In [47]:
if "Model Year" in df_clean.columns:
    df_pd = df_clean.groupBy("Model Year").count().toPandas()
    df_pd["Model Year"] = pd.to_numeric(df_pd["Model Year"], errors='coerce')  # ensure numeric
    df_pd = df_pd.sort_values("Model Year").dropna()

    plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    sns.barplot(x="Model Year", y="count", data=df_pd, palette="Blues_d")
    plt.title("Electric Vehicle Sales by Model Year", fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
    plt.xlabel("Model Year", fontsize=13)
    plt.ylabel("Number of Electric Vehicles", fontsize=13)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
else:
    print("❌ Column 'Model Year' not found.")

# Check if 'Make' column exists
if 'Make' in df.columns:
    # Convert to Pandas
    df_pd = df.select("Make").toPandas()
    
    # Get top 15 brands by sales
    brand_counts = df_pd['Make'].value_counts().reset_index().head(15)
    brand_counts.columns = ['Make', 'Count']
    
    # Plot the bar chart
    import seaborn as sns
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    
    brand_counts.pipe(lambda d: sns.barplot(
        x='Make',
        y='Count',
        data=d,
        palette='Blues_d'
    ))
    
    # Customize plot
    plt.title('EV Sales Distribution Across Major Brands', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
    plt.xlabel('Brand', fontsize=14)
    plt.ylabel('Number of Electric Vehicles', fontsize=14)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='center')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    
else:
    print("❌ Column 'Make' not found.")

# Convert Electric Range column to Pandas
if 'Electric Range' in df.columns:
    df_pd = df.select("Electric Range").toPandas()
    df_pd = df_pd[df_pd['Electric Range'] > 0]  # Filter out invalid values
    
    # Plot Histogram
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    plt.hist(df_pd['Electric Range'], bins=15, color='skyblue', edgecolor='k', alpha=0.7)
    plt.title('Distribution of EV Electric Range', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
    plt.xlabel('Electric Range (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Vehicles')
    plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)
    plt.show()
else:
    print("❌ Column 'Electric Range' not found in dataset.")

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Convert Make column to Pandas
if 'Make' in df.columns:
    df_pd = df.select("Make").toPandas()
    
    # Get top 10 brands by count
    top_brands = df_pd['Make'].value_counts().head(10)
    
    # Plot Pie Chart
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,8))
    plt.pie(top_brands, labels=top_brands.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=140, colors=plt.cm.tab10.colors)
    plt.title('EV Sales Share by Brand (Top 10)', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
    plt.show()

In [51]:
if {"Make","Electric Vehicle Type"}.issubset(df_clean.columns):
    df_pd = df_clean.select("Make","Electric Vehicle Type").toPandas()
    df_pivot = (df_pd.groupby(['Make','Electric Vehicle Type']).size()
                .reset_index(name='Count')
                .pivot(index='Make', columns='Electric Vehicle Type', values='Count')
                .fillna(0))
    
    df_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(14,7), edgecolor='black')
    plt.title("Global EV Sales Performance: Manufacturer vs Vehicle Type", fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
    plt.xlabel("Brands"); plt.ylabel("Total Vehicle Count (Units)")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45); plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
    plt.legend(title='EV Type'); plt.tight_layout(rect=[0,0,0.9,1])
    plt.show()
else:
    print("❌ Columns 'Make' or 'Electric Vehicle Type' not found.")
In [52]:
if {"Make","Electric Range"}.issubset(df.columns):
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    import numpy as np

    df_pd = df.select("Make","Electric Range").toPandas()
    df_pd = df_pd[df_pd['Electric Range']>0]

    codes = df_pd['Make'].astype('category').cat.codes
    names = df_pd['Make'].astype('category').cat.categories
    x = codes + np.random.uniform(-0.15,0.15,len(df_pd))  # jitter

    plt.figure(figsize=(12,7))
    plt.scatter(x, df_pd['Electric Range'], c=codes, cmap='viridis', s=100, alpha=0.7, edgecolors='k')
    plt.title('Electric Vehicle Range Distribution by Manufacturer', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
    plt.xlabel('Manufacturer (Make)', fontsize=14); plt.ylabel('EPA Electric Range (miles)', fontsize=14)
    plt.xticks(ticks=np.arange(len(names)), labels=names, rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.axhline(110, color='r', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='~110 Mile Benchmark')
    plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left'); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()
